SIMPLE: ungracious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ungracious
<hw>Un*gra"cious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
gracious; showing no grace or kindness; being without good will;
unfeeling.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having no grace; graceless; wicked.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not well received; offensive; unpleasing;
unacceptable; not favored.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Anything of grace toward the Irish rebels was as
<qex>ungracious</qex> at Oxford as at London.</q>
<rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*gra"cious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*gra"cious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ungrate</ent>⟦br⟧
